    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genome-annotation-format-comparison/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After assembling the short reads using metaSPAdes40 and genome mining using antiSMASH49, one of the NRPS-PKS gene clusters is assigned as the putative almiramide biosynthetic gene cluster",
      "asbval:note": "antiSMASH is mentioned in the paper as a genome mining tool (passage 6), but it is used for BGC identification in the context of validating DEREPLICATOR+ identifications, not as an input format provider for MetaMiner. The card's claim about antiSMASH .gbk output being used as input to MetaMiner is not supported; the paper uses antiSMASH for genome mining validation, not as a format conversion step for downstream pipelines.",
