    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genome-sequence-mining/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Recently, we introduced DEREPLICATOR for searching spectral datasets against the database of peptidic natural products (PNPs) that include nonribosomal peptides (NRPs), and ribosomally synthesized and post-translationally modified peptides (RiPPs). DEREPLICATOR constructs theoretical spectra of peptide natural products by disconnecting all the bridges and 2-cuts representing amide bonds, and measuring the masses of the connected components.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes DEREPLICATOR for matching RiPPs against mass spectra and mentions genome mining (antiSMASH) for BGC validation, but does not describe a metabologenomic pipeline (MetaMiner) that integrates genomic mining with spectral matching. The paper validates identifications using BLAST search of BGCs against known genomes, but does not present an automated workflow for predicting RiPPs from raw sequences and matching them to spectra.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-018-06082-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "genome-sequence-mining",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply metabologenomic mining to raw nucleotide sequences (FASTA format) or genome assembly output to identify biosynthetic gene clusters (BGCs) and predict novel ribosomally synthesized and post-translationally modified peptides (RiPPs) that can be matched against tandem mass spe",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
