      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We searched all spectra from the following reversed-phase liquid chromatography high-resolution mass spectrometry datasets specified in Supplementary Table 1",
      "asbval:note": "The paper uses LC-MS/MS spectra and mentions antiSMASH for genome mining. However, the paper does not explicitly discuss accepting multiple spectrum formats (MGF, mzXML, mzML, mzData) or BOA as an alternative genome mining tool. The paper focuses on DEREPLICATOR+ which searches spectra against chemical structure databases, not necessarily on constructing databases from genomic input.",
