    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rippp-candidate-structure-generation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DEREPLICATOR constructs theoretical spectra of peptide natural products by disconnecting all the bridges and 2-cuts representing amide bonds, and measuring the masses of the connected components. By applying spectral networks, DEREPLICATOR enabled identification of variants of known PNPs.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes DEREPLICATOR's ability to identify variants of known peptidic natural products (PNPs) and RiPPs through spectral matching, but does not explicitly describe a tool for generating PTM variants from precursor sequences. The paper focuses on spectral matching against existing structures, not on enumerating PTM variants from genome-mined precursors.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-018-06082-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
