    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rippp-candidate-structure-generation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DEREPLICATOR+ enables cross-validation of genome-mining and peptidogenomics/glycogenomics results. While DEREPLICATOR search of GNPS identified hundreds of peptides and their variants, it is limited to dereplicating PNPs and cannot identify other classes of natural products such as polyketides and terpenes.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes DEREPLICATOR's ability to identify variants of known PNPs and enable cross-validation with genome-mining results, but does not describe a tool for enumerating PTM variants from precursor sequences. The paper focuses on matching spectra against existing structures, not generating PTM variants from precursor peptides.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-018-06082-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rippp-candidate-structure-generation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After identifying precursor peptides from genome assemblies via BGC mining, when you need to enumerate the chemical space of PTM variants (lantibiotic, lassopeptide, cyanobactin, or other RiPP classes) before matching tandem mass spectra",
