    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-network-propagation-analysis/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Recently, we introduced DEREPLICATOR for searching spectral datasets against the database of peptidic natural products (PNPs) that include nonribosomal peptides (NRPs), and ribosomally synthesized and post-translationally modified peptides (RiPPs)... DEREPLICATOR constructs theoretical spectra of peptide natural products... By applying spectral networks, DEREPLICATOR enabled identification of variants of known PNPs.",
      "asbval:note": "DEREPLICATOR is confirmed to identify RiPPs and propagate through spectral networks. However, the paper's main focus is on DEREPLICATOR+, not the original DEREPLICATOR. The card describes the original DEREPLICATOR's role, but the paper emphasizes that DEREPLICATOR+ is the improved version that performs this task better.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-018-06082-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-network-propagation-analysis",
